phase2.explanation:
🤖 **Common multi-screen mistakes and fixes.**

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| No state | Use ViewModel or state |
| No data persistence | Save data |
| No error handling | Handle errors |
| Missing callbacks | Pass navigation functions |
| No data passing | Pass arguments |

**Fixes:**
```kotlin
// 1. Use state management
val appState = remember { AppState() }

// 2. Pass navigation callbacks
HomeScreen(
    onNavigateToItems = { navController.navigate("items") }
)

// 3. Pass data
ItemsScreen(
    items = appState.items,
    onItemClick = { navController.navigate("detail/${it.id}") }
)

// 4. Handle errors
try {
    // Navigation
} catch (e: Exception) {
    // Handle error
}
```
